TITLE: Wall Street rally gains momentum, with the Dow surging 700 points
SUMMARY: Stocks rose Tuesday as traders reviewed more corporate earnings reports a day after the market failed to sustain a sharp rally.

TITLE: Crypto developers descend on Paris to party underground at the Catacombs as turmoil grips the industry
SUMMARY: Welcome to the Ethereum Community Conference, an annual event that draws the world's top developers and cryptographers to the City of Light.

TITLE: Google and Chevron invest in nuclear fusion startup that's raised $1.2 billion
SUMMARY: Google, Chevron and a Japanese investment company invest in TAE Technologies, a fusion startup which has raised $1.2 billion so far.

TITLE: UK shatters record for its hottest day ever; London fire service declares 'major incident'
SUMMARY: Britain recorded its hottest-ever day Tuesday, with temperatures hitting a high of 40.3 degrees Celsius (104.5 degrees Fahrenheit) in south England.

TITLE: Russia nears gas shutdown in Europe as Germany rejects claims it can't fulfill contracts
SUMMARY: Germany's energy giant, Uniper, told CNBC it had "formally rejected" Gazprom's force majeure claim.

TITLE: Twitter-Musk trial on $44 billion deal set to begin in October after Musk loses effort to delay
SUMMARY: Twitter on Tuesday won its motion for an expedited trial, set to begin in October, in its lawsuit against Elon Musk.

TITLE: Private jet use is more popular than ever — and first-time buyers are driving record sales
SUMMARY: Business has been booming for some time for major private jet manufacturers.

TITLE: Rolls-Royce and easyJet to test hydrogen combustion engine tech for airplanes
SUMMARY: The firms want to conduct an "early concept ground test" of the hydrogen technology in a Rolls-Royce engine the U.K. later this year.

TITLE: GM reveals electric Chevrolet Blazer priced starting at $45,000
SUMMARY: The 2024 Blazer EV is expected to arrive in showrooms beginning next summer, with starting pricing between about $45,000 and $66,000.

TITLE: A can of Coca-Cola for $13? Prices are rising on one of Europe's most popular islands
SUMMARY: Though Spain is generally considered a reasonably priced travel destination, the island of Ibiza has long been known as a place for living the high life.

TITLE: Apple agrees to pay up to $395 to MacBook owners who replaced 'butterfly' keyboards
SUMMARY: The settlement brings a close to an infamous era in Apple product design.

TITLE: UK outlines net-zero aviation plan on hottest-ever day, says travelers can keep flying 'guilt-free'
SUMMARY: The U.K. government's so-called "Jet Zero" strategy comes as Britain reported its hottest day on record.

TITLE: Yellen says the U.S. and its allies should use ‘friend-shoring’ to give supply chains a boost
SUMMARY: The term draws on the concepts of "onshoring" and "nearshoring," which refer to the transferring of supply chains back home or closer to home.

TITLE: Looking to get your funds out of a collapsed crypto platform? Don't get your hopes up
SUMMARY: Bankruptcy filings from Celsius and Voyager have raised questions about what happens to investors' funds when a crypto platform fails.

TITLE: Nuclear power plant lowers output to protect fish as Europe grapples with heatwave
SUMMARY: The news out of Switzerland comes as parts of Europe grapple with a significant heatwave.

TITLE: China holdings of U.S. debt fall below $1 trillion for the first time since 2010
SUMMARY: China's holdings of U.S. debt have fallen below $1 trillion for the first time in 12 years. Rising rates have made Treasurys potentially less attractive.

TITLE: UK plans $95 million hydrogen gigafactory to produce components for vehicles
SUMMARY: Operations at the plant are planned to start in the first half of 2024.

TITLE: TikTok owner ByteDance explores self-designed chips as China aims for semiconductor self-sufficiency
SUMMARY: ByteDance's semiconductor push highlights a focus from firms to create chips for specific purposes as well as China's desire to become stronger in this tech.

TITLE: A stronger Singapore dollar may be exactly what the country needs to battle inflation, says Barclays
SUMMARY: A stronger Singapore dollar is likely to weigh on export momentum, but it may be "precisely" what the country needs to cool inflation, an economist told CNBC.

TITLE: SoftBank reportedly pauses plan for Arm's London listing
SUMMARY: SoftBank has stopped working on a London initial public offering for chip designer Arm because of political upheaval in the U.K., the Financial Times reported.

TITLE: The food security crisis could kill more people than Covid has, says Senegal minister at G-20
SUMMARY: Countries hoarding, imposing export restrictions and refusing to trade Russian food are worsening the food security crisis.

TITLE: Price cap on Russian oil is a 'ridiculous idea' and could push oil to $140, says energy research group
SUMMARY: Gal Luft of the Institute for the Analysis of Global Security said a price cap would be like visiting a shop and asking the seller to accept less money.

TITLE: Goldman CEO David Solomon says inflation is 'deeply entrenched' in the global economy
SUMMARY: Uncertainty has Goldman CEO David Solomon operating cautiously as central banks around the world tighten financial conditions to combat inflation, he said.

TITLE: Netflix investors brace for subscriber losses as company works on long-term fixes
SUMMARY: The theme of Netflix's quarterly earnings Tuesday may be minimizing bad news rather than showcasing good news.

TITLE: 'Unprecedented urgency' may have pushed India and the EU to revive trade talks after 9 years
SUMMARY: In a stunning turnaround, India and the European Union recently revived negotiations for a free trade agreement after talks halted nearly a decade ago.

TITLE: Goldman Sachs is looking at reinstating year-end job cuts as economic outlook dims
SUMMARY: Wall Street firms have long culled those deemed to be underperformers, often at the end of the year as they prepare to dole out bonuses to those who remain.

TITLE: Twitter fires back at Elon Musk's attempt to delay trial
SUMMARY: Twitter accused the Tesla CEO of using delay tactics to harm the company in the court of public opinion.

TITLE: 9/11 families condemn Trump for hosting Saudi-funded LIV golf tournament at his NJ club
SUMMARY: Members of the advocacy group 9/11 Justice condemned Trump for hosting a tournament for the Saudi-funded LIV golf league at his club in Bedminster, N.J.

TITLE: Nikola adjourns shareholder meeting, again, as founder Trevor Milton blocks stock-issue plan
SUMMARY: Nikola is trying to win enough shareholder votes to overcome ex-CEO Trevor Milton's objection to issuing new stock.

TITLE: IBM shares slide after company trims cash forecast
SUMMARY: The hardware, software and consulting provider trimmed its 2022 free cash flow forecast.
